page.title: 03One square kilometre
page.content: For the domesday book our group visited the rural area of Putsborough and our group is Claire ,Emma, Duncan Sims and Robin .Putsborough sands is one of the best beaches on the coast of England with miles of golden sand. Our village is in a valley.Land off the beach is protected from development by the national trust so it remains unspoilt.Putsborough manor with its thatched roof dates back to the domesday book which makes the manor around 900 years old. below, one of the fields was being ploughed up by a tractor, a sheep dog running a long side it and a flight of gulls behind it.
